</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C277A9558129FF812E19FD7002C5FD15" blockId="5.[317,1270,651,993]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">The revision and the identification key to the species groups and the species were made by HIRSCHMANN (1991).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8AD2FADE8129FF812E19FD2A0393FBF5" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph id="C277A9558129FF812E19FD2A033FFCA5" blockId="5.[317,1270,651,993]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
The main characteristics of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="05C8D2D68129FF812C35FD2A038CFD36" authorityName="BERLESE" authorityYear="1884" box="[850,930,721,747]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachyuropodidae" genus="Oplitis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F0BC75478129FF812C35FD2A038CFD36" box="[850,930,721,747]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Oplitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the following (HIRSCH- MANN 1993): Idiosoma: Shape oval or circular, idiosoma small. Gnathosoma: Corniculi short and horn-like. Laciniae with some branches and covered by long hairs. Three to five serrated branches on the base of epistome. Tritosternum with serrated margin. Chelicerae with nodus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C277A9558129FF812E19FC7A01A7FC3C" blockId="5.[317,1270,651,993]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="05C8D2D68129FF812E19FC7A0207FC46" box="[382,553,897,923]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachyuropodidae" genus="Oplitis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="F0BC75478129FF812E19FC7A01E0FC46" box="[382,462,897,923]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Oplitis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
are known from Europe, North and South America, and Asia, and they are widely distributed in the west and east Ethiopian region (WIŚNIEWSKI 1993).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C277A9558129FF812E19FBF50393FBF5" blockId="5.[382,957,1038,1064]" box="[382,957,1038,1064]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<typeStatus id="1D7317F78129FF812E19FBF50194FBF5" box="[382,442,1038,1064]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<emphasis id="F0BC75478129FF812D41FBF502C3FBF5" box="[550,749,1038,1064]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<taxonomicName id="05C8D2D68129FF812D41FBF50258FBF5" authorityName="BERLESE" authorityYear="1884" box="[550,630,1038,1064]" class="Arachnida" family="Trachyuropodidae" genus="Oplitis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Oplitis</taxonomicName>
paradoxa
</emphasis>
(BERLESE, 1884)
</paragraph>
